x4freetext: MP tandem accelerator
The reaction products were analysed with the
Munich Q3D spectrograph. The acceptance opening of
the spectrograph was 10.89 msr. A 1.8 m long focal
plane detector which made both deltaE-E particle
identification and position determination was used.
The target consisted of 122 mu-g/cm**2 122Te
evaporated on a 4.2 mu-g/cm**2 carbon foil, and had
an isotopic enrichment of 91.2%,the contaminants being
other stable Te isotopes with masses between 123 and
130, none of them exceeding 1.91%.
DWBA analysis was performed.
